      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I'm selling my absolute pride and joy. This car is in incredible shape\u2014honestly, it looks and feels like it just rolled off the lot. I've babied it since day one, kept it garage-stored, and stayed on top of every single service. It\u2019s spotless inside and out, and it drives like a dream. If you're looking for something that\u2019s been truly loved and is ready for a new home, this is the one! Feel free to reach out with any questions\u2014I'd love to chat!",
      "price": 45500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox. Mechanically flawless, the rod bearing service and VANOS overhaul have been preemptively completed. The rear subframe has been professionally reinforced with Turner Motorsport plates to ensure structural integrity under high lateral G-loads. Riding on factory Style 67 forged alloys wrapped in fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber, the suspension remains tight with upgraded Bilstein B6 dampers. The interior is a time capsule, boasting Nappa leather with zero bolster wear and a functional Harmon Kardon audio suite. No leaks, no codes, and a comprehensive service history. A true collector-tier example of the ultimate driving machine.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
